quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  12,104,even though You do not demand any recompense for this information. This Qur’an is nothing but a reminder for all the people of the worlds
  12,105,There are many signs in the heavens and the earth which they pass by; yet they pay no attention to them
  12,106,As a result most of them who believe in Allah also commit shirk
  12,107,"Do they feel secure that Allah’s scourge will not fall on them, or that the Hour of Doom will not come upon them suddenly while they do not suspect it"
  12,108,"Tell them plainly: \"This is my way. I invite you to Allah with sure knowledge which I and my followers possess. Glory be to Allah, and I am not one of the pagans"
  12,109,"All the Messengers that We sent before you, O Muhammad, were human beings, to whom We sent Our Revelations after choosing them from the people of their town. Have these unbelievers not traveled through the land and seen what was the end of those who passed away before them? From their destiny you should know that the home of the hereafter is better for those who are righteous. Why don’t you understand"
  12,110,"Respite was granted until the Messengers gave up hope of their people and realized that they were being treated as liars, Our help came to them and We delivered those whom We pleased; and Our scourge was not averted from the criminal people"
  12,111,"There is a lesson in these stories of former people for the men of common sense. This story of Joseph revealed in the Qur’an is not an invented tale, but a confirmation of previous scriptures - a detailed exposition of all things, and is a guidance and blessing for the people who believe"